Good friend, replied Brisena, that may you do so long as you think good; at present we have no other news of him, than that he is gone in search of his brother Amadis, who is lost, we know not for what cause; and she then related how Guilan had found the arms.
Hearing this, she began to weep, and say, O Lord God, what will become of my Lord and friend Don Florestan!
for he so loves that brother, that, if he finds him not, he also will become desperate, and I shall never see him more!
