take thy arms, and defend thyself if thou canst.
I might do it with some doubt against others, he replied, but can have none in opposing thee, who art so full of pride and threats.
Then they ran their course; both felt the shock; the horse of Beltenebros reeled, and he himself was wounded at the nipple of his breast.
