With this answer the Damsel returned; and Beltenebros took his arms, and rode to an open part of the field to wait for the encounter.
The first who came was the one who had such an inclination to win his horse.
Beltenebros was pleased that this was the first: he unhorsed him, and bade Enil take his horse, and said, Sir Knight, if you keep your word, you will not have another fall for a whole year, for so you promised unless you won my bay; but he lay groaning, for he had three ribs and a hip broken.
